{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017ukihadxpHaZFr4ZveHnby","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The existing nodes have no custom allocation attributes. I need to:\n\n1. Add a custom allocation attribute (e.g., `node.attr.rack: rack1`) to the existing nodes (by updating their config)\n2. Create new data nodes with `node.attr.rack: rack2`\n3. Create the `app-data` index with routing filtered to `rack2`\n\nBut wait - updating existing nodes requires restarting them, which would require modifying the ConfigMap and then rolling restart. That's complex.\n\nAn alternative approach:\n1. Create a new ConfigMap for the new data nodes with `node.attr.zone: hot` or `node.attr.tier: new`\n2. Create a new StatefulSet for the additional data nodes with 2 replicas using this ConfigMap\n3. Tag the new nodes with `node.attr.zone: new` while leaving the existing nodes without this attribute, or add `node.attr.zone: original` to them\n4. Create the `app-data` index and configure shard routing to prefer the new nodes\n\nThe constraint requires the new nodes to have a different allocation attribute than the originals. Since the existing nodes don't currently have custom attributes, I could either update them to add `node.attr.zone: original` while the new ones get `node.attr.zone: new`, or just leave the existing nodes as-is and only tag the new ones.\n\nOption B is simpler and avoids disrupting the cluster with rolling restarts, so I'll go with that—the new nodes will have `node.attr.zone: new` while the existing ones have no zone attribute. Though for cleaner verification, adding the attribute to existing nodes too would be more explicit, even if it requires a rolling restart.\n\nActually, the cleanest path forward is to leave the existing nodes untouched and create a separate ConfigMap and StatefulSet for the new data-only nodes with the zone attribute set. Then I'll create the app-data index and configure index-level routing to require the new zone, which will ensure shards get placed on those nodes.\n\nSince the cluster uses TLS, the new nodes need access to the same certificate secret that's already in place. They'll also need the same app label so they can discover and join the existing cluster through the headless service.\n\nCreating the new ConfigMap and StatefulSet... Writing ConfigMap for new nodes...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1333,"cache_read_input_tokens":34637,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1333},"output_tokens":15,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9181a7ab-a6ac-4103-9133-64c91afb6cb6","uuid":"68d38ee8-fda6-4af4-9f95-4d14709ff264","request_id":"req_011CcQS35YcfkmJ1nWCgvNwJ"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017ukihadxpHaZFr4ZveHnby","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. I need to:\n1. Create a new ConfigMap for the 2 new data nodes with a `zone: new` attribute\n2. Create a new StatefulSet `es-data` (separate from `es`) with 2 data-only replicas\n3. Create the `app-data` index routed to the new nodes\n\nLet me check the TLS certs and then build the new nodes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1333,"cache_read_input_tokens":34637,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1333},"output_tokens":15,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9181a7ab-a6ac-4103-9133-64c91afb6cb6","uuid":"588ffb9f-b143-4e63-9b37-6565a3cfa122","request_id":"req_011CcQS35YcfkmJ1nWCgvNwJ"}
